{
  "text": "Photoelicitaton is derived from visual sociology, whereas projective assessment originated in psychoanalysis. Photoelicitation is usually used as part of an ethnographic research project in combination with participant observation and in-depth interviews [CITATION_1] . It consists of providing informants with photographs of social situations, and having subjects describe the events in the photographs.",
